ror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Matilde de Saint-John was born in 1067, in Normandy, France, her father, Thomas De St. John, was 27 and her mother, Mrs Thomas St John, was 26. She married Hugo de Talemasche in 1089, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 5 sons. She died in 1090, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 23."},"et":{"1067–1090":"1067–1090","1070–1154":"1070–1154","1090–1151":"1090–1151","1110–1179":"1110–1179","1115–1151":"1115–1151","1117–1179":"1117–1179","1119–Male":"1119–Surnud","1040–Male":"1040–Surnud","1042–Female":"1042–Surnud","1090":"1090","before 1067":"enne 1067","1110":"1110","1154":"1154","1042":"1042","1151":"1151","1040":"1040","1070":"1070","1117":"1117","1115":"1115","1179":"1179","1067":"1067","1089":"1089","1119":"1119","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Europe":"Europe","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Stoke Talmage, Oxfordshire, England":"Stoke Talmage, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Talmage Stoke, Oxfordshire,, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1067–1090":"1067–1090","1070–1154":"1070–1154","1090–1151":"1090–1151","1110–1179":"1110–1179","1115–1151":"1115–1151","1117–1179":"1117–1179","1119–Male":"1119–Kuollut","1040–Male":"1040–Kuollut","1042–Female":"1042–Kuollut","1090":"1090","before 1067":"ennen vuotta 1067","1110":"1110","1154":"1154","1042":"1042","1151":"1151","1040":"1040","1070":"1070","1117":"1117","1115":"1115","1179":"1179","1067":"1067","1089":"1089","1119":"1119","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Europe":"Europe","Normandy,